WEBVTT

00:00:00.260 --> 00:00:02.000
Hello and welcome back.

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:06.880
In this lesson, I will show you how to use Claude code to add a fallback model.

00:00:06.880 --> 00:00:12.120
A fallback model is the model that OpenClaw will automatically use when the primary model

00:00:12.120 --> 00:00:15.480
becomes rate-limited or unavailable.

00:00:15.480 --> 00:00:20.080
Head over to the OpenRouter list of free models.

00:00:20.080 --> 00:00:25.640
Remember that we can list the free models by typing in free in the search box.

00:00:25.640 --> 00:00:31.160
In the previous lesson, we have already set NVIDIA's Nemotron as the primary model.

00:00:31.160 --> 00:00:39.950
Nemotron is a 120 billion parameter model with 1 million context.

00:00:39.950 --> 00:00:47.090
DeepSeek V4 Flash is a 284 billion parameter model with 1.05 million context.

00:00:47.090 --> 00:00:48.470
Both are good.

00:00:48.470 --> 00:00:55.840
Let's use DeepSeek V4 Flash free as the fallback model.

00:00:55.840 --> 00:01:08.820
First, we copy the official name and paste it into Notepad.

00:01:08.820 --> 00:01:14.640
Then we list the existing models using the command openclaw models list.

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:18.120
We can see that the default model is Nemotron.

00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:22.600
We also have DeepSeek V4 Pro which is a paid model.

00:01:22.600 --> 00:01:27.580
And we also have GPT 5.4 which is also a paid model.

00:01:27.580 --> 00:01:32.480
Note that although we already have these other models, they are not automatically set as

00:01:32.480 --> 00:01:34.120
fallback models.

00:01:34.120 --> 00:01:39.800
Now we want to add deepseek 4 flash free from open router as the fallback.

00:01:39.800 --> 00:01:42.100
Let's run claude desktop.

00:01:42.100 --> 00:01:48.740
If you don't have a claude subscription, then use codex, it will also work just fine.

00:01:48.740 --> 00:01:51.460 
Just follow along in this lesson using codex.

00:01:51.460 --> 00:01:55.380
But for this lesson, I will use claude code.

00:01:55.380 --> 00:02:05.460
Search for claude and pin it to the taskbar, so that in future, it is easier for us to

00:02:05.460 --> 00:02:18.000
find it.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:22.960
Make sure you are on the Code tab, since we want to use Claude Code.

00:02:22.960 --> 00:02:28.620
Just ignore this warning, it is from one of my previously set up MCP server from a different

00:02:28.620 --> 00:02:31.960
course.

00:02:31.960 --> 00:02:36.080
Let's get the path to where OpenClaw is installed.

00:02:36.080 --> 00:02:42.800
We want to give this path to Claude Code.

00:02:42.800 --> 00:02:51.100
It is normally a hidden folder because it has a dot in front of the name OpenClaw.

00:02:51.100 --> 00:02:53.580
Then type in the prompt.

00:02:53.580 --> 00:02:57.500
You can download this prompt from the resource section for this lesson.

00:02:57.500 --> 00:03:01.860
However, note that you need to change the paths to match your machine.

00:03:01.860 --> 00:03:07.100
The prompt should contain all the relevant information needed to add DeepSeek V4 Flash

00:03:07.100 --> 00:03:09.020
as a fallback model.

00:03:09.020 --> 00:03:14.240
Also, be sure to tell Claude Code not to remove any existing models. 

00:03:14.240 --> 00:03:19.300
Also inform it where the previously saved API keys are found and that you have already

00:03:19.300 --> 00:03:22.840
set the OpenRouter API keys and you want to use that.

00:03:22.840 --> 00:03:28.280
If you do not know the path to the file, it is okay, just ask Claude Code to look for the

00:03:28.280 --> 00:03:35.440
authprofiles.json file.

00:03:35.440 --> 00:03:49.190
I will show you where the authprofiles.json file is found.

00:03:49.190 --> 00:03:53.710
You should also tell Claude Code that you want the ability to switch to the fallback model

00:03:53.710 --> 00:04:10.150
and set it as the default model at any time in future.

00:04:10.150 --> 00:04:28.640
Click Send and let Claude Code work its magic.

00:04:28.640 --> 00:04:41.570
Whenever it asks you for permission, just click Always Allow.

00:04:41.570 --> 00:04:46.010
After a while, it reports back saying that it has made the changes.

00:04:46.010 --> 00:04:54.720
Let's read what it says.

00:04:54.720 --> 00:05:00.440
The important part says when Nemotron fails or rate limits, OpenClaw will hand off to

00:05:00.440 --> 00:05:07.190
DeepSeek V4 Flash automatically.

00:05:07.190 --> 00:05:25.470
Now we open a command prompt to restart the OpenClaw gateway.

00:05:25.470 --> 00:05:28.850
After restarting, we open Telegram.

00:05:28.850 --> 00:05:36.920
I have cleared the chat history and typed in slash new to get a new session.

00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:42.920
Meanwhile, we open the command prompt and list the models.

00:05:42.920 --> 00:05:48.580
Back in telegram, I had asked it what model are you on and it replies that it is on nemotron

00:05:48.580 --> 00:05:49.580
free.

00:05:49.580 --> 00:05:54.420
I then asked it what is its fallback model and it says that the fallback is deepseek

00:05:54.420 --> 00:05:56.600
v4 flash free.

00:05:56.600 --> 00:05:59.320
So it works.

00:05:59.320 --> 00:06:06.820
Also the models listing also confirms that deepseek v4 flash free is the fallback model.

00:06:06.820 --> 00:06:12.820
Note that you could also have done the same thing using codex.

00:06:12.820 --> 00:06:17.100
The next thing to do is to take a snapshot of this virtual machine.

00:06:17.100 --> 00:06:23.820
First, we will shut down this virtual machine.

00:06:23.820 --> 00:06:28.120
In VirtualBox Manager, click on button Take to take a snapshot.

00:06:28.120 --> 00:06:30.220
Give it a suitable name.

00:06:30.220 --> 00:06:36.820
For example, Backup set to DeepSeek V4 Flash Free.

00:06:36.820 --> 00:06:42.820
You can also delete any previous snapshots in order to recover some disk storage space.

00:06:42.820 --> 00:06:49.180
So this is how you can use Claude Code or Codex to set up a fallback model.

00:06:49.180 --> 00:06:54.820
Remember you could also use them to configure anything else or to troubleshoot and fix any

00:06:54.820 --> 00:06:55.820
issues.

00:06:55.820 --> 00:06:58.060
That's all for this video.

00:06:58.060 --> 00:06:58.900
Thanks for watching.

